				</div>
				<div class="project" data-aos="fade-down">
					<div class="project-image">
						<img src="weather-app.png" />
					</div>
					<div class="project-details">
						<div class="project-header">
							<h3>Weather App</h3>
							<ul class="project-tags">
								<li>Personal</li>
								<li>React</li>
								<li>JavaScript</li>
								<li>APIs</li>
								<li>HTML</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="project-summary">
							<p>
								Ravenhall Sports Centre is my most extensive personal project, a
								WordPress website I designed and developed for a small business
								client located in the western suburbs of Melbourne. This was my
								first client-based project where I learnt a substancial amount
								of lessons in the process.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="button-container">
							<a href="/projects/weather-app"><button>VIEW PROJECT</button></a>
							<a href="/weather-app" target="_blank"><button>DEMO</button></a>
							<a href="https://github.com/avn-j/weather-app" target="_blank"
								><button>GITHUB</button></a
							>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="project" data-aos="fade-down">
					<div class="project-details">
						<div class="project-header">
							<h3>Car Sharing Web Application</h3>
							<ul class="project-tags">
								<li>University</li>
								<li>React</li>
								<li>JavaScript</li>
								<li>NoSQL</li>
								<li>APIs</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="project-summary">
							<p>
								My capstone project for university. A responsive web application
								for a fictitious car-sharing service called "Car Pirates", where
								users can choose to pick up cars within the area and drop them
								off anywhere after usage.
							</p>
						</div>
						<a href="/car-pirates"><button>VIEW PROJECT</button></a>
					</div>
					<div class="project-image">
						<img src="car-pirates.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="project" data-aos="fade-down">
					<div class="project-image">
						<img src="everyday-desserts.png" />
					</div>
					<div class="project-details">
						<div class="project-header">
							<h3>Everyday Desserts</h3>
							<ul class="project-tags">
								<li>University</li>
								<li>HTML</li>
								<li>CSS</li>
								<li>PHP</li>
								<li>JavaScript</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="project-summary">
							<p>
								Everyday Desserts is a fictitious dessert-kit service for an
								eBusiness university course. The purpose of the project was to
								explore the idea of building an eCommerce platform that sold
								products, focusing heavily on creating a customer-first design.
							</p>
						</div>
						<a href="/everyday-desserts"><button>VIEW PROJECT</button></a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="about-me-container">
				<div class="about-me-title" data-aos="fade-down">
					<h2><a name="projects">About Me</a></h2>
					<svg
						width="35"
						height="35"
						viewBox="0 0 24 24"
						fill="none"
						xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
					>
						<path
							d="M11.0001 3.67157L13.0001 3.67157L13.0001 16.4999L16.2426 13.2574L17.6568 14.6716L12 20.3284L6.34314 14.6716L7.75735 13.2574L11.0001 16.5001L11.0001 3.67157Z"
							fill="currentColor"
						/>
					</svg>
				</div>
				<div class="about-me">
					<div class="personal-description" data-aos="fade-right">
						<h3>More About Myself</h3>
						<p>
							My name is Aevan Josh. I am an aspiring full-stack developer
							looking for job opportunities to develop my web development
							skills. I'm passionate about cutting-edge, responsive, and
							captivating web experiences with thoughtful user interfaces.
						</p>
						<p>
							My journey in web development began when I was tinkering with
							basic HTML and CSS websites at a young age including submitting
							English assignments in a website form during early high school.
							From there my passion flourished; I began creating small projects
							involving basic JavaScript to landing my first role in web
							development. Building staple features for eCommerce websites as a
							Graduate Web Developer.
						</p>
						<p>
							My current role does not involve any web development experience
							although I have learned many skills that apply to the industry
							including working with an agile workflow and interacting with
							clients. My current goal is to switch my career path back to the
							web development space and contribute to innovative projects.
						</p>
						<h3 style="margin-top: 5rem">Technical Skills</h3>
						<p>
							These are some of the technologies I have worked with
							professionally:
						</p>
						<ul class="technical-skills" data-aos="zoom-in">
							<li>HTML</li>
							<li>CSS</li>
							<li>JavaScript</li>
							<li>Java</li>
							<li>VueJS</li>
							<li>TypeScript</li>
							<li>NodeJS</li>
							<li>NuxtJS</li>
							<li>TailwindCSS</li>
							<li>MySQL</li>
							<li>NoSQL</li>
							<li>AWS</li>
							<li>Git</li>
							<li>Shell Scripting</li>
							<li>REST APIs</li>
						</ul>
						<p>
							These are some of the technologies I have dabbled with in past
							personal and university projects:
						</p>
						<ul class="technical-skills" data-aos="zoom-in">
							<li>ReactJS</li>
							<li>PHP</li>
							<li>Python</li>
							<li>C#</li>
							<li>Figma</li>
							<li>Adobe Photoshop</li>
							<li>11ty</li>
							<li>Bootstrap</li>
							<li>Firebase</li>
							<li>Postgres</li>
							<li>Flask</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
